t command. \n\nAssuming the output is not null, the next step would be to get the profile ID. But since this is part of the cron job, the agent should follow the steps outlined in SOUL.md. \n\nWait, the user's message is the cron task, so the agent's job is to execute the steps. The response should be a summary of the actions taken. If the queue is empty, say \"Queue empty.\" and exit. If there's a request, process it. \n\nLet me check the tools available. The exec function is available. So I need to call exec with the command \"node /data/img-gen/img-claim.js img-gen-4\". Then, based on the output, proceed. \n\nBut the user's instruction says: \"Return your summary as plain text; it will be delivered automatically.\" So the agent should output the result of the queue check. If there's a request, process it. If not, say queue is empty.\n\nSince this is a cron job, the agent should run the command and return the result. But the user's instruction says to follow the SOUL.md workflow. So if there's a request, the agent should generate the image. However, the user is asking for a summary of the queue check. The cron job is to check the queue and process pending requests. So the agent should report whether the queue is empty or if there are requests to process.\n\nWait, the user says: \"If a request is returned (not null), process it following your SOUL.md workflow. Generate the image in Gemini, download it, call img-complete.js when done, then check the queue again for more pending requests.\"\n\nSo the task is to run the claim script, and if there's a request, process it. The summary should be a plain text response. So the agent needs to run the claim script and check if there's a request. If yes, process it and report. If not, say queue is empty.\n\nLet me structure this. First, run the claim command. If the output is not null, process the request. If null, return \"Queue empty.\"\n\nBut the user is asking for a summary as plain text. So the agent's response should be